State Manager at Kloud Solutions. Developing and managing the Victorian consulting business leveraging a career in IT encompassing development, architecture, project management and team leadership of large-scale and complex projects. Worked with and for leading organisations across multiple industry sectors with a particular focus on Internet, Cloud and financial markets. Attributes include:
•	Ability to define and drive strategy, direction, mentoring and leadership across business and technology;
•	Strong leadership of IT practitioners with proven experience in building teams and competencies;
•	Excellent verbal and written communication skills and an ability to communicate across various levels of the business and technology, backed by a deep technical understanding and capability.
•	Proven experience delivering enterprise solutions across the Software Development Lifecycle performing equally across process-driven waterfall and agile project environments;

Specialties: Architecture, Agile, Communications, Cloud, Web, Scale, Performance, Identity, Security, Finance, Trading, Realtime Processing, Azure, SharePoint, BizTalk, .NET

Interested in the intersection of economics, green technology and the limitless opportunity of a world powered by Cloud computing.

jobs.description:
Computershare is a large financial services company focused on delivering leading IT solutions via the Technology Services arm. This IT group consists of some 1000 employees delivering solutions from the same global platforms, tools and application solutions.
Working within a team of 6 architects responsible for delivering guidance and architecture to global enterprise platform projects delivered to regional development teams. The role required creation and presentation of global IT group strategy and subsequent overseeing of solutions aligned with those strategies. Each taken from inception, justification, costing, through to design and development with:
•	Creation of guidance and strategy materials, including Vision, Mission and Strategy Map to align and focus development effort;
•	Lifecycle estimation and costing of new business opportunities and related IT solutions; 
•	Delivery of High-performance multilingual Content Management System on Sharepoint 2010 platform; 
•	Delivery of centralised Identity and Access Management system supporting federation and single sign-on between multiple organisations;
•	Design of a high performance investor portal based on MVC Framework;
•	Implementation of a highly scalable web application based on Windows Azure Cloud platform for effectively serving highly unpredictable web traffic cost.

Delivering to the common needs of six independent regionalised and geographically dispersed web development teams through centralised development tools, libraries, standards and processes. 
Responsible for a team of 6 who developed shared libraries and applications for:
•	Authentication and Authorisation: producing an application security product which controls access to all the company’s internet-facing applications. Written in .NET technologies and implementing role-based security and SAML single sign-on;
•	MarketData: designing, implementing and supporting the corporate market data system using Reuters RIS service redistributed using high performance, cached .NET WebServices;
•	Content Management: creating a high performance multilingual content management system replicated globally with full approval workflow system;
•	Reporting an Monitoring: a large (Tb) MS SQL database with OLAP cubes presented through Excel and SSRS reports;
•	Application Blocks: a library of common web development components for maximising reuse across regional development teams;
•	Process: implementing a software development process and tools for managing and auditing the roll-out of code through to testing, handover and production. The tools initially using CVS were rewritten for TFS and the daily build and unit testing system.

